snippet.textDisplay: Man your dentist did suck. When I had mine taken out I told them how I was scared and wished I could be knocked out for it. They said no problem. Come the day of the operation, anxiety sky rocketing to heights never known before, sat in the chair and they hooked me up to an EKG. Now I was extremely scared. Then they put an IV line in me and injected something. "This will knock you out" I sat there, wondered when It would work, then passed out. I did wake up half way through but was numb so I didn't care and they knocked me out again. The worst part was I ended up getting a REALLY bad infection in my right cheek, so bad the side of my face looked like it had a tennis ball in it. I ended up having to go back. They numbed me (which REALLY hurt thanks to the infection making my face tender), then they just took a knife to my mouth and sliced it open on the inside and push all the pus and blood out (btw, I was numb but still had taste, and the taste of blood and pus was the worst thing I have ever tasted). Then when that was done they gave me special mouthwash and I was good. Still never want to do it again.
